abstract: Amy Klobuchar is deploying her Minnesota hot dish at voter house parties, but it may be a hard sell outside her home state.
snippet: Amy Klobuchar is deploying her Minnesota hot dish at voter house parties, but it may be a hard sell outside her home state.
lead_paragraph: Hot dish, the Minnesota-specific church-supper stalwart that cooks in other parts of the country might mistake for a casserole, is no stranger to hard work.

abstract: He doesn’t want a revolution. He doesn’t have a movement. He could still win this thing.
snippet: He doesn’t want a revolution. He doesn’t have a movement. He could still win this thing.
lead_paragraph: Joe Biden has no trouble lingering in place, wherever he is, especially if there’s a point he wants to finish — or start. Generally it does not matter how many people are prodding him along or waiting out in the cold. And it seemed important to Biden that I hear what he was talking about right now before we finished.

abstract: Iowa caucusgoers aren’t just asking about the one issue that’s dominating the headlines.
snippet: Iowa caucusgoers aren’t just asking about the one issue that’s dominating the headlines.
lead_paragraph: MARSHALLTOWN, Iowa — With three jurors in the impeachment trial traipsing about Iowa this past weekend, you’d expect someone — anyone! — planning to attend the Iowa caucuses to ask the presidential candidates about impeachment.

abstract: John Bolton’s new memoir is titled “The Room Where It Happened,” nearly the same as a song from Lin-Manuel Miranda’s Broadway hit.
snippet: John Bolton’s new memoir is titled “The Room Where It Happened,” nearly the same as a song from Lin-Manuel Miranda’s Broadway hit.
lead_paragraph: Wait a minute. A lyric from a Broadway show is part of the most heated political discourse of the moment? Something from a musical has actually been appended to a major national talking point?

abstract: Senator Tom Cotton, Republican of Arkansas, rubbed his eyes with his right hand and yawned.
snippet: Senator Tom Cotton, Republican of Arkansas, rubbed his eyes with his right hand and yawned.
lead_paragraph: The slow start to the trial had some senators inside the chamber visibly struggling to remain engaged with President Trump’s lawyers.
headline_main: Senators yawn and take notes as the defense team talks.
